transcripts:
[MUSIC PLAYING]

Hey! one of my favorite onions to work with, the leek. Of course I like to start with a santoku. It's a great knife, beveled, vegetables fall right off. Get the the tip on the cutting board and do a nice easy rock. Now, I like to get right into these. You can see some of that dirt; you can wipe that off with a towel. Just wanna flatten them out. It's a little darker so you want to cook it. Look at that, pretty hu?. Now, if you want to take it to the next level, just take a few of those. Say you want a little garnish for that soup. That beautiful stack you did with those leeks. So we got coins, matchsticks, diced, and trim.
